FBIS3-47626 "dreas010_d_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 South Korea Prosecutor-General To Set Up International Crime Office SK1401021194 Seoul THE KOREA HERALD in English 14 Jan 94 p 2 SK1401021194 Seoul THE KOREA HERALD Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Prosecutor-General's Office will set up a new department to deal mainly with international criminal affairs, a spokesman said yesterday. The prosecution will also appoint a prosecutor at each district prosecution office who will exclusively handle crimes by foreigners, international disputes over intellectual property rights, and criminal affairs related to tariff and foreign currencies, he said. Meanwhile, the Justice Ministry yesterday said it plans to dispatch prosecution officials to the Korean Embassies at Geneva and the United Nations who will provide legal advice.
